{
  "text": "We further investigated the possibility whether PGF 2a directly stimulates the recruitment of PMNs into the CL. As Liptak et al. already showed that the bovine immune cells had no FPr mRNA [CITATION_1] , PMNs as well as PBMCs did not express PGF 2a receptor mRNA and protein (Fig. 7) . Moreover, PGF 2a injection in vivo did not change the response level of PMN migration stimulated by IL-8 (Fig. 7D) , suggesting that PGF 2a injection did not change the capacity/sensitivity of PMN migration. Thus, PGF 2a cannot directly attract immune cells into the CL, and the rapid and local induction such as P-selectin and IL-8 by PGF 2a within the CL is the key component to induce PMN migration in cows.",
